        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 5:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is wrongly quoted as a parallel. There the Baptist ‘hath borne witness to the truth,’ i.e. to the Gospel or to Christ. Here the brethren bare witness to Gaius’s truth, i.e. to his Christian life, as is shewn by what follows. The ‘thy’ is emphatic, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
