  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Vers. 3, 4.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "For I rejoiced greatly.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " We must not lose sight of the \"for,\" which is full of meaning. The elder has just expressed a wish that the external well-being of Gains may equal the well-being of his soul; and he is quite sure of the latter, for brethren keep coming and bearing witness to the fact. The good report of Gains is still greater joy to the apostle than the evil report of Diotrephes is a sorrow to him. The language in condemnation of Diotrephes, severe as it is, is not so strong as this in thankful delight respecting Gaius: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Greater joy have I none than",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "(to hear of)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "these things.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " \"Greater\" is made doubly emphatic, first by position at the beginning of the sentence, and secondly by the double comparative ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "μειζοτέραν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". 3 John 1:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
